{{Politics of the European Union}}
The '''Directorate-General for Translation''' ('''DGT'''), located in [[Brussels]] and [[Luxembourg City|Luxembourg]], provides [[translation]] of written text into and out of the [[European Union]]'s twenty-four [[Languages of the European Union|official languages]]. With an annual output of about 1.5 million pages, it is the largest translation service in the world, employing some 1,750 linguists.


