'''Hosam al-Din Ali Bitlisi Nurbakhshi''' (died 1494-1495) was a [[Kurds|Kurdish]] [[Sufism|Sufi]] author. He was the father of the noted historian [[Idris Bitlisi]].{{sfn|Yazici|2004|page=490}} 

Nothing is known about Hosam al-Din's early life, except for the fact that he received a proper education and was well versed in both [[Persian language|Persian]] and [[Arabic language|Arabic]].{{sfn|Yazici|2004|page=490}} Either prior to completing his education, or after that, he became a member of the Sufi [[Noorbakshia Islam|Nurbakhshi]] order.{{sfn|Yazici|2004|page=490}} The Nurbakhshi order itself was a branch of the [[Kubrawiya|Kobrawiya]] order (founded by [[Najmuddin Kubra|Najm al-Din Kobra]]).{{sfn|Yazici|2004|page=490}} It is considered likely that Hosam al-Din became a follower, and in turn the eventual successor of the so-called "actual" founder of the order; [[Shah Syed Muhammad Nurbakhsh Qahistani|Mohammad Nurbakhsh]] (died 1465).{{sfn|Yazici|2004|page=490}}

He died in [[Bitlis]] in 1494-1495, and was buried there.{{sfn|Yazici|2004|page=490}}

