{{Infobox language | name = Kogi | nativename = ''Kággaba'' | states = [[Colombia]] | region = [[Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta]] | ethnicity = [[Kogi people|Kogi]] | speakers = {{sigfig|9910|2}} | date = 2004 | ref = e18 | speakers2 = nearly all monolingual | familycolor = American | fam1 = [[Chibchan language|Chibchan]] | fam2 = Arwako–Chimila | fam3 = Arwako | iso3 = kog | glotto = cogu1240 | glottorefname = Cogui }}
'''Kogi''' (Cogui), or '''Kagaba''' (Cágaba), is a [[Chibchan language]] of [[Colombia]]. The [[Kogi people]] are almost entirely monolingual, and maintain the only unconquered [[Andean civilization]].
