'''Magne Rommetveit''' (4 October 1918 – 6 January 2009) was a Norwegian lexicographer.
He was born in [[Stord]]. He [[examen artium|finished]] his secondary education in [[Voss]] in 1940 and took the [[cand.philol.]] degree in 1950. He worked as a lexicographer associated with the [[University of Oslo]], and eventually became a [[docent]] and professor of Nynorsk philology from 1978 to 1988. He was involved in ''[[Nynorskordboka]]'' and ''[[Norsk Ordbok (Nynorsk)|Norsk ordbok]]'', but his main work was the agricultural lexicon ''Norsk landbruksordbok''. Commencing the work in 1955, it was published at [[Det Norske Samlaget|Samlaget]] in 1978 with 80,000 entries. He later wrote the more popular book on Nynorsk synonyms, ''Med andre ord''. Published in 1985 as a follow-up of the earlier ''På godt norsk'', it was reissued several times.<ref name=dt1>{{Cite news|title=Magne Rommetveit til minne|last=Lie|first=Tove|date=16 January 2009|work=Dag og Tid|page=27|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref name=dt2>{{Cite news|title=Magne Rommetveit (1918–2009)|last=Lægreid|first=Erling|authorlink=Erling Lægreid|date=16 January 2009|work=Dag og Tid|page=12|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref name=nm>{{cite web|url=http://www.nm.no/tekst.cfm?id=2783|title=Magne Rommetveit er død|last=Lothe|first=Hege|date=9 January 2009|publisher=[[Noregs Mållag]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=5 June 2014}}</ref>
He was a co-founder of several [[Nynorsk]] institutions in [[Oslo]]: [[Kringkastingsringen]] which fought for Nynorsk use in the [[NRK]], where he was general manager from 1955 to 1970; the weekly newspaper ''[[Dag og Tid]]'' in 1962 for which he coined the name; and the news agency [[Nynorsk Pressekontor]] in 1969.<ref name=dt1/><ref name=dt2/> He became an honorary member of [[Noregs Mållag]] in 1998.<ref name=nm/>
