'''Shashikala Manandhar''' (born 1960) is an award-winning [[Nepal]]ese novelist. The first female novelist writing in the [[Nepal Bhasa]] language, she also writes in Nepali.<ref name="award">{{cite news|url=http://www.nepalnews.com.np/contents/englishdaily/ktmpost/2003/jan/jan16/local1.htm |title=Ganki Basundhara Award given away |date=2003-01-16 |work=[[The Kathmandu Post]] |publisher=nepalnews.com |accessdate=2008-08-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040803150752/http://www.nepalnews.com.np/contents/englishdaily/ktmpost/2003/jan/jan16/local1.htm |archivedate=August 3, 2004 }}</ref>
Manandhar was born in 1960 in Nepal's capital of [[Kathmandu]].<ref name="layalama">{{cite web|url=http://www.layalama.com/writers%20profiles.htm |title=Writer's Profiles |work=Layalama.com |accessdate=2008-08-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071028083309/http://www.layalama.com/writers%20profiles.htm |archivedate=October 28, 2007 }}</ref> She is a postgraduate in [[Master of Science|MS]].<ref name="award" /> Her first novel was ''Shaili'', published in 1985.<ref name="award" /> although by then she had published ''Nami'' in 1982,<ref name="layalama" /> a collection of short stories; and other literary publications.<ref name="award" /> On 15 January 2003 Manandhar was awarded the prestigious Ganki-Basundhara Award by the Ganki-Basundhara Award Academy.<ref name="award" />
